==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warm-blooded
<hw>Warm"-blood`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Having warm blood; -- applied especially to
those animals, as birds and mammals, which have warm blood, or, more
properly, the power of maintaining a nearly uniform temperature whatever
the temperature of the surrounding air. See
<er>Homoiothermal</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warmer</ent>⟦br⟧
